ates that the dephasing due\nto the second order self-forces for quasi-circular E(I)MRIs may be well\ncaptured by the 3PN energy flux, once we obtain all the spin dependent terms,\nexcept for the case with an extremely large spin of the central Kerr black.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Oct 2012 11:39:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 8 Jan 2013 20:09:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-01-09"}
